Electrocomponents, T&L, Severn Trent: U.K., Irish Equity Preview

-- B y   J o h n   S i m p s o n
-- 
2011-05-26T23:01:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-26/electrocomponents-t-l-severn-trent-u-k-irish-equity-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
that may have unusual share-price changes in U.K. and Irish
markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses and prices are from
the last market close.  The benchmark FTSE 100 Index gained 10.85 points, or 0.2
percent, to 5,880.99. The FTSE All-Share Index rose 0.2 percent
to 3,064.66, while Ireland’s ISEQ fell 0.3 percent to 2,926.45.  Severn Trent Plc (SVT)  : The U.K.’s second-largest water
company may report full-year net income of 196 million pounds
($321 million) according to the average of 6 estimates compiled
by Bloomberg. The shares rose 1 percent to 1,502 pence.  Tate & Lyle Plc (TATE)  : The maker of the low-calorie
sweetener Splenda may report full-year net income of 101 million
pounds, according to the average of 6 estimates compiled by
Bloomberg. The stock rose 0.8 percent to 608.5 pence.  Electrocomponents Plc (ECM)  : The world’s largest
distributor of electronics and maintenance products may report
full-year net income of 77.3 million pounds, according to the
average of 5 estimates compiled by Bloomberg. The shares rose
0.4 percent to 285.2 pence.  To contact the reporter on this story:
